<br>
Thus, spell casters have to kill everything at range or die. There's little room for mistakes. Instead of allowing casters a better chance to avoid interruption, Mythic went the other way around the problem and just made them even more dependant on range for survival by increasing the effectiveness of their spells, then resists came into play nerfing the casters.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile, the root of the problem is that casters are so easily interrupted that they are better off swinging a staff than trying to cast spell when someone gets within striking distance.<br>
